Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da yin barazanar da ke nuna cewa ta yi wa arna wa'azi
Mako guda bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani labarin shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka inda ta ce an dakatar da ayyukan kasuwanci tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafofin watsa labarai na Amurka wajen yada farfaganda.
A ranar Laraba, shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi nuni da rahoton da jaridar China Daily ta fitar a Des Moines Register - jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa - bayan da ya zargi kasar Sin da kokarin shiga zaben 'yan majalisar wakilai na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba a Amurka, zargin da China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing ta yi kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka alama ce, kamar yadda jami'an Amurka suka fada wa Reuters, na sabon sauyi a shirin zaben Washington na kokarin matsa lamba kan China.
Duk da cewa al'adar gwamnatocin kasashen waje ne su yi karin bayani don kokarin hana tallace-tallace, Beijing da Washington suna cikin yakin cinikayya da ke kara tsanantawa, wanda ya haifar da karin haraji kan kayayyakin da kasashen biyu ke shigowa da su.
An gabatar da takunkumin ramuwar gayya na kasar Sin a farkon yakin cinikayya don kawar da masu fitar da kaya a jihohi kamar Iowa, wanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, in ji masana na kasar Sin da na Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa China, ya ce Beijing tana biyan harajin ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni.
China, Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wani labarin ra'ayi a cikin ranar Lahadi Des Moines Register,  yana ƙarfafa game da farin ciki ta buga bayanan farfaganda a cikin 'yan jaridarmu kyauta.
"Ta hanyar yada farfagandar ta, China ta yi wa al'adun Amurka da suka fi muhimmanci, da 'yancin magana da kuma 'yancin latsa, ta hanyar buga bayanai a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"Dangane da kwatancen, a cikin kantunan sayar da jaridu a kan titi a nan Beijing, za ka iya samun muryoyi masu iyaka, masu fadi da kuma rashin tunani mai ma'ana game da ra'ayoyi masu banbanci da mutanen China ke da su game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin, saboda jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin tana kula da kafofin watsa labarai", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa wasu daga cikin manyan jaridu a kasar Sin sun ki amincewa da buga labarinsa, amma bai bayyana inda jaridar take ba.
